title: Bug 109350: Output parameter not displayed in data set dialog
OB: When calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database and storing the query result in an output parameter as an object, the data set dialog does not display the output parameter.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the data set dialog.
SR:
To reproduce the bug: 
1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database. 
2. Store the query result in an output parameter as an object. 
3. Open the data set dialog. The output parameter should be displayed there.
